<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2013-08-13</DATELINE><TITLE>Spiking the MERS-coronavirus receptor</TITLE><BODY>A novel coronavirus, the Middle East respiratory syndrome coronavirus, recently emerged through zoonotic transmission, causing a severe lower respiratory tract infection in humans. In two recent papers, one published in Cell Research, the crystal structure of the viral receptor-binding domain in complex with the host CD26/dipeptidyl peptidase 4 receptor has now been characterized.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>